 Will Pay:**\n\t+ Network Provider: 20% coinsurance\n\t+ Out-of-Network Provider: 40% coinsurance\n* **Limitations, Exceptions, & Other Important Information:**\n\t+ Cost sharing does not apply for preventive services. Depending on the type of services, a coinsurance may apply. Maternity care may include tests and services described elsewhere in the SBC (i.e., ultrasound).\n\n### If you need help recovering or have other special health needs\n\n* **Services You May Need:**\n\t+ Home health care\n\t+ Rehabilitation services\n\t+ Habilitation services\n\t+ Skilled nursing care\n\t+ Durable medical equipment\n\t+ Hospice services\n* **What You Will Pay:**\n\t+ Network Provider: 20% coinsurance\n\t+ Out-of-Network Provider: 40% coinsurance\n* **Limitations, Exceptions, & Other Important Information:**\n\t+ 60 visits/year for home health care and rehabilitation services\n\t+ Includes physical therapy, speech therapy, and occupational therapy\n\t+ Excludes vehicle modifications, home modifications, exercise, and bathroom equipment for durable medical equipment\n\t+ Preauthorization is required for hospice services. If you don't get preauthorization, benefits could be reduced by 50% of the total cost of the service.\n\n### If your child needs dental or eye care\n\n* **Services You May Need:**\n\t+ Children's eye exam\n\t+ Children's glasses\n\t+ Children's dental check-up\n* **What You Will Pay:**\n\t+ Network Provider: $35 copay/visit for eye exam, 20% coinsurance for glasses, no charge for dental check-up\n\t+ Out-of-Network Provider: Not covered\n* **Limitations, Exceptions, & Other Important Information:**\n\t+ Coverage limited to one exam/year for eye exam\n\t+ Coverage limited to one pair of glasses/year for glasses\n\t+ None for dental check-up\n\n--- PAGE 3 END ---\n[DATA TABLE SUMMARY: **Common Medical Event Summary**\n=====================================\n\n### If you have a hospital stay\n\n* **Services You May Need:**\n\t+ Facility fee (e.g., hospital room)\n\